  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Full Time Dance Instructor",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a full-time ballet instructor. The instructor’s roles include:</p><ul><li>Plan, prepare and teach assigned classes according to the Royal Academy of Dance (RAD) syllabus and/or under the directive of the Principal.</li><li>Keep updated with developments in the RAD syllabus and teaching resources, and make relevant changes to class plans and activities.</li><li>Prepare, coach and register students for RAD examinations including examinations groupings and scheduling.</li><li>Present during the RAD examinations period to supervise students who are attending examinations or assisting other teachers, as assigned by the Principal/Management.</li><li>Manage student behavior in the classroom by establishing appropriate dance pedagogy methods to create a conducive learning experience for students.</li><li>Observe, evaluate and maintain accurate and complete records of student’s progress and development, and provide feedback on work and students’ progress to the Principal.</li><li>Communicate regularly to students and parents regarding student’s progress where necessary.</li><li>Attend staff/teachers and parents’ meetings, as and when necessary.</li><li>Assist, teach, and/or conduct coaching and rehearsals during ad-hoc events/activities organized by the Academy such as school concert/rehearsals, public performance, workshops, dance competitions, and masterclasses.</li><li>Any other duties assigned by the School Principal</li><li>General admin tasks relating to teaching and student matters including,</li><li>Prepare referral letters as and when required.</li><li>Distribute or hand out notices and documents related to teaching, class or Academy activities.</li><li>Preparation of class plan for relief teachers, scheduling mock and actual RAD examinations.</li><li>Preparation of annual progress report for students.</li><li>Assist Principal in planning annual school timetable.</li><li>Maintain accurate class attendance record for every class.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Preferably with Diploma/Degree in Dance and/or Certificate in Ballet Teaching Studies (CBTS) teaching qualifications for Royal Academy of Dance (RAD). Candidates with substantiate experience in teaching ballet will also be considered.</li><li>Preferably with prior experience as a professional ballet dancer.</li><li>Minimum two to three years of experience in teaching ballet.</li><li>Comfortable with teaching students of all ages.</li><li>Fluent in English.</li><li>Motivated, passionate and reliable with strong work ethic.</li></ul><p>\n</p>",
